        {
            "id": "https://textexpander.com/?p=8763",
            "url": "https://textexpander.com/blog/how-to-solve-common-recruiting-problems",
            "title": "How to Solve Common Recruiting Problems: 5 Common Challenges",
            "content_html": "<a href=\"https://textexpander.com/blog/how-to-solve-common-recruiting-problems\"><img width=\"600\" height=\"400\" src=\"https://textexpander.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/tebanner-recruiting-chall-600x400.jpeg\" alt=\"How to Solve Common Recruiting Problems: 5 Common Challenges\" align=\"left\" style=\"margin: 0 20px 20px 0;max-width:560px;max-width:100%;\" /></a>\n<p>With the U.S. economy reaching \u201cthe <a href=\"https://www.dol.gov/oasam/programs/history/herman/reports/futurework/conference/trends/trendsV.htm\">lowest unemployment rates</a> in 30 years,\u201d filling open positions with the best qualified candidate has become a major challenge.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Additionally, 77% of CEOs are concerned that <a href=\"https://www.cnbc.com/2017/01/18/four-concerns-that-keep-ceos-awake-at-night.html\">skills shortages could hinder</a> their organization\u2019s growth.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Here are several novel solutions for five of the most common challenges facing today\u2019s recruiter.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>Challenge 1: Limited talent pool</h2>\n\n\n\n<h3>Situation</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>The Internet has made it easier for recruiters to find people with a strong <a href=\"https://techterms.com/definition/digital_footprint\">digital footprint</a> online, using LinkedIn, social media and traditional job boards.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Still, a whopping 60 million Americans either <a href=\"https://www.recode.net/2017/6/20/15839626/disparity-between-urban-rural-internet-access-major-economies\">lack internet access</a> or <a href=\"http://www.pewresearch.org/fact-tank/2018/03/05/some-americans-dont-use-the-internet-who-are-they/\">choose not to use</a> the internet, making countless workers inaccessible online.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Solution</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Consider <a href=\"https://maishacannon.com/sourcing-unplugged-offline-strategies-cc8750202613\">offline sourcing</a> to find pools of untapped talent. Offline sourcing involves researching events online and then attending in person with the hiring team.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Use <a href=\"http://www.meetup.com\">Meetup</a>, <a href=\"http://www.eventbrite.com\">Eventbrite</a> and <a href=\"http://www.10times.com\">10Times</a> to discover local events of relevance to attend.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Continue your offline search by partnering with community based organizations and alumni career centers to effectively expand both your professional network and your candidate pool.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>Challenge 2: Getting ghosted by candidates</h2>\n\n\n\n<h3>Situation</h3>\n\n\n\n<p><a href=\"https://www.johnleonard.com/blog/how-to-avoid-getting-ghosted-by-candidates\">Ghosting</a> is when someone unexpectedly, without explanation goes silent or disappears.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>As <a href=\"https://www.entrepreneur.com/article/320500\">Jim Stroud</a> notes, \u201cghosting is highly unprofessional and ultimately costs both employers and job seekers.\u201d</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Solution</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>To improve no\u2011show rates, consider an automated scheduling tool like <a href=\"https://textexpander.com/entry/textexpander-crossover-set-up-meetings-faster-with-textexpander-and-calendly/\">Calendly</a>. Calendly allows you to set up appointments and send email or text reminders.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Glen Cathey\u2019s <a href=\"http://booleanblackbelt.com/2015/07/sourcing-recruiting-candidate-funnel-output-calculators/\">recruiting funnel calculator</a> can help recruiters determine how many people will need to be identified to result in one hire.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Having knowledge of this data will help ensure that if the perfect candidate suddenly disappears, there will be ample options in the pipeline.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>Challenge 3: Nonresponsive hiring managers</h2>\n\n\n\n<h3>Situation</h3>\n\n\n\n<p><a href=\"https://drjohnsullivan.com/articles/the-top-12-reasons-why-slow-hiring-severely-damages-recruiting-and-business-results/\">Slow hiring</a>, especially due to nonresponsive hiring managers, can cause recruiters to lose high-quality, in-demand candidates.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Hiring managers who fail to provide prompt feedback negatively impact the candidate experience, frustrate recruiters and hinder their own team\u2019s progress.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Solution</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>During the kickoff meeting, set deadlines and expectations to hold both recruiter and hiring managers accountable throughout the process.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Take note of any planned vacation and ask for a backup interviewer who can serve as a contact in the hiring manager\u2019s absence. Be sure to calendar the next weekly check-in before your kickoff meeting ends.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>When delivering weekly updates, go beyond the standard text email and deliver digestible data with tools like <a href=\"https://public.tableau.com/en-us/s/\">Tableau Public</a>, <a href=\"https://talentwall.io/\">Talent Wall</a> and <a href=\"http://www.canva.com\">Canva</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Create a private <a href=\"http://www.slack.com\">Slack</a> channel for key roles and add relevant stakeholders for visibility and collaboration.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Use <a href=\"http://www.zoom.us\">Zoom</a> or <a href=\"https://appear.in/\">Appear.In</a> to regularly review resumes with your hiring manager in real time.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>Challenge 4: No time to source</h2>\n\n\n\n<h3>Situation</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>A day in the life of a recruiter involves attending meetings with internal stakeholders, enforcing HR policies, and handling everything from interviews to negotiating offers. This leaves little time for sourcing passive candidates.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><a href=\"https://tsi-corp.com/product/the-sourcing-method/\">Shally Steckerl</a> defines sourcing as the specialized discipline of proactively identifying and engaging with talent not found via traditional means.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Solution</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>To get the most return on your sourcing investment, optimize your time with proven productivity hacks like <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pomodoro_Technique\">The Pomodoro Technique</a> or <a href=\"https://www.forbes.com/sites/kevinkruse/2017/04/19/why-highly-productive-people-use-time-blocking/#72608d2065e1\">time blocking</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Explore <a href=\"https://toggl.com/time-blocking/\">Toggl</a> and <a href=\"https://tomato-timer.com/\">Tomato Timer</a> to optimize your time.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Use <a href=\"http://www.textexpander.com\">TextExpander</a> to create shortcuts for your most frequently used Boolean strings, target companies or skills.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>Challenge 5: Engaging sourced prospects</h2>\n\n\n\n<h3>Situation</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>With an <a href=\"https://www.socialtalent.com/blog/recruitment/10-mind-blowing-sales-statistics-that-will-help-your-recruit-smarter\">average LinkedIn InMail response rate</a> of 28%, engaging prospects has become as difficult as identifying them in a tight market.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Solution</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>To increase your email and InMail response rates, consider using a tool like <a href=\"https://sendcheckit.com/email-subject-line-tester\">Send Check It</a> to A/B test your subject lines or <a href=\"https://www.perrymarshall.com/grade/\">Perry Marshall</a> to measure message readability.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Getting inspiration from a <a href=\"https://textexpander.com/blog/linkedin-message-templates-recruiting/\">tried and true InMail template</a> can give you head start.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>It\u2019s also useful to look to other industries for inspiration for your toughest challenges.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><a href=\"https://blog.hubspot.com/marketing/make-emails-more-clickable-list\">Marketing</a>, for example, offers impactful insights applicable to engaging sourced prospects. <a href=\"https://agilemanifesto.org/principles.html\">Agile software development</a> principles can help refresh a stagnant hiring process.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Finally, using a tool like <a href=\"https://www.textrecruit.com/\">TextRecruit</a> allows you to leverage text messaging, live online chat and artificial intelligence to hire better people, faster.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>Your Recruiting Obstacles</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>What is your biggest recruiting challenge? Let us know in our <a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/groups/TextExpander\">Facebook</a> group or on <a href=\"https://twitter.com/TextExpander\">Twitter</a>.</p>\n",
            "content_text": "With the U.S. economy reaching \u201cthe lowest unemployment rates in 30 years,\u201d filling open positions with the best qualified candidate has become a major challenge.\n\n\n\nAdditionally, 77% of CEOs are concerned that skills shortages could hinder their organization\u2019s growth.\n\n\n\nHere are several novel solutions for five of the most common challenges facing today\u2019s recruiter.\n\n\n\nChallenge 1: Limited talent pool\n\n\n\nSituation\n\n\n\nThe Internet has made it easier for recruiters to find people with a strong digital footprint online, using LinkedIn, social media and traditional job boards.\n\n\n\nStill, a whopping 60 million Americans either lack internet access or choose not to use the internet, making countless workers inaccessible online.\n\n\n\nSolution\n\n\n\nConsider offline sourcing to find pools of untapped talent. Offline sourcing involves researching events online and then attending in person with the hiring team.\n\n\n\nUse Meetup, Eventbrite and 10Times to discover local events of relevance to attend.\n\n\n\nContinue your offline search by partnering with community based organizations and alumni career centers to effectively expand both your professional network and your candidate pool.\n\n\n\nChallenge 2: Getting ghosted by candidates\n\n\n\nSituation\n\n\n\nGhosting is when someone unexpectedly, without explanation goes silent or disappears.\n\n\n\nAs Jim Stroud notes, \u201cghosting is highly unprofessional and ultimately costs both employers and job seekers.\u201d\n\n\n\nSolution\n\n\n\nTo improve no\u2011show rates, consider an automated scheduling tool like Calendly. Calendly allows you to set up appointments and send email or text reminders.\n\n\n\nGlen Cathey\u2019s recruiting funnel calculator can help recruiters determine how many people will need to be identified to result in one hire.\n\n\n\nHaving knowledge of this data will help ensure that if the perfect candidate suddenly disappears, there will be ample options in the pipeline.\n\n\n\nChallenge 3: Nonresponsive hiring managers\n\n\n\nSituation\n\n\n\nSlow hiring, especially due to nonresponsive hiring managers, can cause recruiters to lose high-quality, in-demand candidates.\n\n\n\nHiring managers who fail to provide prompt feedback negatively impact the candidate experience, frustrate recruiters and hinder their own team\u2019s progress.\n\n\n\nSolution\n\n\n\nDuring the kickoff meeting, set deadlines and expectations to hold both recruiter and hiring managers accountable throughout the process.\n\n\n\nTake note of any planned vacation and ask for a backup interviewer who can serve as a contact in the hiring manager\u2019s absence. Be sure to calendar the next weekly check-in before your kickoff meeting ends.\n\n\n\nWhen delivering weekly updates, go beyond the standard text email and deliver digestible data with tools like Tableau Public, Talent Wall and Canva.\n\n\n\nCreate a private Slack channel for key roles and add relevant stakeholders for visibility and collaboration.\n\n\n\nUse Zoom or Appear.In to regularly review resumes with your hiring manager in real time.\n\n\n\nChallenge 4: No time to source\n\n\n\nSituation\n\n\n\nA day in the life of a recruiter involves attending meetings with internal stakeholders, enforcing HR policies, and handling everything from interviews to negotiating offers. This leaves little time for sourcing passive candidates.\n\n\n\nShally Steckerl defines sourcing as the specialized discipline of proactively identifying and engaging with talent not found via traditional means.\n\n\n\nSolution\n\n\n\nTo get the most return on your sourcing investment, optimize your time with proven productivity hacks like The Pomodoro Technique or time blocking.\n\n\n\nExplore Toggl and Tomato Timer to optimize your time.\n\n\n\nUse TextExpander to create shortcuts for your most frequently used Boolean strings, target companies or skills.\n\n\n\nChallenge 5: Engaging sourced prospects\n\n\n\nSituation\n\n\n\nWith an average LinkedIn InMail response rate of 28%, engaging prospects has become as difficult as identifying them in a tight market.\n\n\n\nSolution\n\n\n\nTo increase your email and InMail response rates, consider using a tool like Send Check It to A/B test your subject lines or Perry Marshall to measure message readability.\n\n\n\nGetting inspiration from a tried and true InMail template can give you head start.\n\n\n\nIt\u2019s also useful to look to other industries for inspiration for your toughest challenges.\n\n\n\nMarketing, for example, offers impactful insights applicable to engaging sourced prospects. Agile software development principles can help refresh a stagnant hiring process.\n\n\n\nFinally, using a tool like TextRecruit allows you to leverage text messaging, live online chat and artificial intelligence to hire better people, faster.\n\n\n\nYour Recruiting Obstacles\n\n\n\nWhat is your biggest recruiting challenge? Let us know in our Facebook group or on Twitter.",
